Not sure if there is a cleaner way, but you could achieve something like this with [maps](https://sass-lang.com/documentation/values/maps). One way would be to define your button classes as keys of a map that hold another map of the actual colors to be used:

```
$button-colors: (

  &quot;primary&quot;: (
    background: #f5f5f5,
    color: #fff
  ),
  
  &quot;secondary&quot;: (
    background: #000,
    color: #333
  )
  
);
```

Then in your mixin your  `$argument` would be a text value instead of a hex value and you could access the button color map:

```
@mixin button-style($argument) {
  
  $color-map: map-get($button-colors, $argument);
  
  background: map-get($color-map, background);
  color: map-get($color-map, color);
  
}
```

The mixin would then be consumed like this:

```
.button-primary {
 @include button-style(primary)
}

.button-secondary {
 @include button-style(secondary)
}
```

